<body>
	<h1>CS2102 Template: <%= title%></h1>
	<h2>Tutorial</h2>
	In this tutorial, we will use loops to create the table instead of copying with different column values.<br />
	The <code class="highlighter-rouge">ejs</code> segment will be using <code
		class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;%&nbsp;%&gt;</code> instead of the standard HTML tags.<br />
	- Within the <code class="highlighter-rouge">ejs</code> tags, you can write some <code
		class="highlighter-rouge">JavaScript</code> code.<br />
	We start with the assumption that there exists a variable called <code class="highlighter-rouge">data</code> which is
	an array of object with three fields: matric, name, and faculty.<br />
	To loop through this <code class="highlighter-rouge">data</code>, we need to add the following code:<br />
	<code class="language-html" data-lang="html">
		&lt;% for (var i=0; i&lt;data.length; i++) { %&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; HTML BODY<br />
		&lt;% } %&gt;</code><br />
	- In the <code class="highlighter-rouge">HTML BODY</code>, we can create each individual rows by using the following
	code:<br />
	<code class="language-html" data-lang="html">
		&lt;tr&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;td&gt;&lt;%= data[i].matric%&gt;&lt;/td&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;td&gt;&lt;%= data[i].name%&gt;&lt;/td&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;td&gt;&lt;%= data[i].faculty%&gt;&lt;/td&gt;<br />
		&lt;/tr&gt;</code><br />
	- The use of <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;%= data[i].matric%&gt;</code> retrieves the value of the field <code
		class="highlighter-rouge">matric</code> from the <code class="highlighter-rouge">data</code>.<br />
	- Since this is within the loop, all the values within the <code class="highlighter-rouge">data</code> will be created
	as a row.<br />
	You can see the example below.<br /><br />
	<h2>Loops</h2>
	<table class="table">
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th scope="col">Matric</th>
				<th scope="col">Name</th>
				<th scope="col">Faculty</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<% for(var i=0; i<data.length; i++) { %>
			<tr>
				<td><%= data[i].matric%></td>
				<td><%= data[i].name%></td>
				<td><%= data[i].faculty%></td>
			</tr>
			<% } %>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	<h3>CODE:</h3>
	<code class="language-html" data-lang="html">
		&lt;table class="table"&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;thead&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;tr&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;th scope="col"&gt;Matric&lt;/th&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;th scope="col"&gt;Name&lt;/th&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;th scope="col"&gt;Faculty&lt;/th&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;/tr&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;/thead&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;tbody&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;% for(var i=0; i&lt;data.length; i++) { %&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;tr&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;td&gt;&lt;%= data[i].matric%&gt;&lt;/td&gt;<br />
		&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;td&gt;&lt;%= data[i].name%&gt;&lt;/td&gt;<br />
